When measuring the ratio of population to provider, a higher ratio means less providers per capita, implying less access.

Sullivan County (3,070:1) had the highest ratio of residents to primary care providers. and the number of providers continues to decrease since 2019. Westchester County had the best resident to provider ratio (760:1). Westchester and Rockland (1,880:1) had better ratios than NYS (1,240:1). \[see Figure 20\]

